HEADWORD: lonesomeness
<hw>lone"some*ness</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a disposition
toward being alone.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> aloneness, loneliness, solitude.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The condition of being alone; the feeling of sadness
resulting from being alone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lone-Star State</ent>⟦br⟧
